0009|- [HelpText]
0010|*Using ready-made sucros
0012|*When working with the Survo Editor, sucros are called normally
0013|*by activating the name of the sucro with a `/' in front of the name
0014|*and a list of parameters after the name.
0015|*Thus a typical sucro call is
0017|*/SUCRO1 DATA3,VAR5
0019|*Since sucros are not regular Survo operations, their functions are not
0020|*usually described in this inquiry system. However, a common practice is that
0021|*a sucro gives information on itself by activating it without parameters
0022|*or with a `?' as the only parameter. Thus
0023|*/SUCRO1 ?
0024|*should tell about the functions of sucro SUCRO1. This information will be
0025|*written in the edit field and it may overwrite text below the current line.
