0066|- [HelpText]
0067|*Teaching programs
0069|*In sucros made for teaching of Survo functions or for teaching of
0070|*various Survo applications, it is important to control the pace of the
0071|*process. Since such teaching programs present real activities,
0072|*it should always be possible for the user to interrupt the run and
0073|*continue on his/her own from the setup generated by the sucro so far.
0075|*Thus any sucro (made for teaching) can be stopped by pressing the '.'
0076|*key. A temporary interrupt is achieved by the space bar. Another
0077|*press of the space bar makes the sucro to continue.
0078|*To slow down the speed, the '-' key is pressed (a couple of times).
0079|*The original speed is resumed by pressing '+' equally many times.
0080|*Many teaching programs have their own internal speed control and there
0081|*should be no urgent need for using the '+' and '-' keys.
0083|*The basic speed of a teaching program can be set more accurately
0084|*by the sucro command
0085|*/WAITSET <slowness_parameter>
S   |          <                  >
0086|*where the default value is 10.
0089|- [NAME(TUTSOUND)][/NAME] / qtu6_03.html#TUTSOUND TUTSOUND?
0090|- [New]
0091|*Interrupts and sound signals in sucros:
0092|- [/New]
0093|*A teaching program can be temporarily interrupted by pressing ','.
0094|*During interruption it is possible to scroll the current edit field and
0095|*activate various operations (but not sucros!).
0096|*Thereafter the teaching program may be continued from the interrupt
0097|*position by pressing keys F2 and ','.
0099|*Any sound signal can be activated during a sucro by PLAY SOUND commands.
0101|*Certain acoustic warnings and signals are automatically specified
0102|*by a line 'tut_sounds' in SURVO.APU.
0104|*'tutsound' gives a list consisting of names of 3 sound (VAW) files
0105|*tut_sounds=<sound1>,<sound2>,<sound3>
S   |            <      > <      > <      >
0106|*where
0107|*<sound1> is heard when the user hits a wrong key when pressing of
S   | <      >
0108|*         a particular key is prompted by the tutorial,
0109|*<sound2> indicates that an interrupt takes place (when the user has
S   | <      >
0110|*         pressed the ',' key),
0111|*<sound3> tells that user has pressed keys F2 and ',' in order to
S   | <      >
0112|*         let the tutorial to be continued.
0113|*All sound files must be located in the <Survo>\U\SND directory.
S   |                                        <     >
0114|*The current default setting is
0115|*tut_sounds=PROTECT,CARBRAKE,DRIVEBY
