0145|*Key sucros
0147|*Sucros having one-letter names are called key sucros because instead
0148|*of normal activation (by /X for example) a sucro X can also be called
0149|*without visible traces by the key combination PREFIX M X
0150|*Typical macros of Survo have been made as key sucros. For example,
0151|*sucro X changes the position of the current word by the next one on
0152|*the same line. In such a task it is important to invoke the action
0153|*without typing any command.
0154|*A list of key sucros and other sucro tools is obtained by activating
0155|*the sucro
0156|*/SUCROS
0158|- [New]
0159|*Another set of key sucros having names #X (X=any letter) but called
0160|*by the key combination
0161|- [/New]
0162|*PREFIX N X
0163|- [New]
0164|*are reserved for users' own applications.
